# **AGNTCY × libp2p: Networking Foundations and Collaboration Opportunities**

> *A collaborative overview of how AGNTCY currently leverages libp2p, and areas where the libp2p community can contribute to future interoperability, observability, and networking research.*

---

## Introduction

As members of the libp2p community, we have been exploring how AGNTCY's networking architecture is built and where there are opportunities for deeper collaboration.

This document summarizes our understanding of the current implementation based on the AGNTCY source code and documentation. It is intended as a technical and community resource, and we welcome corrections, suggestions, and discussion from both the AGNTCY and libp2p communities.

Rather than viewing libp2p as simply another dependency, we see it as one of the foundational networking layers enabling AGNTCY's decentralized architecture.

---

# Why libp2p?

Building distributed systems requires solving a number of difficult networking problems:

* Secure peer authentication
* Peer discovery
* Routing
* NAT traversal
* Connection management
* Reliable messaging
* Transport negotiation
* Resource management

libp2p provides these as reusable building blocks, allowing applications to focus on higher-level protocols instead of implementing networking primitives from scratch.

For AGNTCY, this means the project can focus on agent discovery, identity, and protocol interoperability while relying on a mature networking stack underneath.

---

# Our Understanding of the Current Architecture

Based on the current implementation, AGNTCY's Directory (DIR) service uses libp2p across several networking layers.

```text
                   Agent Directory

                 Agent Metadata
                       │
                       ▼
                  Content Addressing
                     (IPFS CID)
                       │
                       ▼
               libp2p Kad-DHT Advertisement
                       │
                       ▼
                Provider Discovery
                       │
                       ▼
                Peer Discovery
                       │
                       ▼
                libp2p RPC Retrieval
                       │
                       ▼
                Agent Communication
```

The implementation combines several libp2p components:

| Component      | Purpose                                 |
| -------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| libp2p Host    | Peer identity and secure networking     |
| Kad-DHT        | Distributed peer and provider discovery |
| GossipSub      | Announcement propagation                |
| RPC            | Metadata retrieval between peers        |
| Peer IDs       | Cryptographic node identity             |
| Multiaddresses | Reachable network addresses             |
| IPFS CID       | Immutable content identifiers           |

