# Key Areas Where libp2p Is Used

Our review identified libp2p usage throughout the networking stack.

## Peer Identity

Every DIR node becomes a libp2p peer with

* cryptographic identity
* peer ID
* transport configuration
* multiaddresses

---

## Distributed Discovery

Kad-DHT provides

* provider advertisements
* peer routing
* content routing
* decentralized discovery

This allows agent metadata to be discovered without requiring centralized lookup services.

---

## Metadata Retrieval

Once a peer has been discovered through the DHT,

libp2p RPC is used to retrieve

* labels
* metadata
* routing information

This separates discovery from metadata transfer, reducing unnecessary DHT traffic.

---

## Event Distribution

GossipSub is used to announce newly published records across participating peers.

This allows newly available agent information to propagate quickly throughout the network.

---

## Content Addressing

AGNTCY uses IPFS Content Identifiers (CIDs) as immutable references for agent records.

Rather than storing metadata directly inside the DHT, the DHT advertises providers for CID-addressed content.

---

# End-to-End Discovery Flow

A simplified view of the discovery pipeline looks like:

```text
OCI Registry
      │
      ▼
Artifact
      │
      ▼
CID
      │
      ▼
libp2p Kad-DHT
      │
      ▼
Provider Discovery
      │
      ▼
Peer Discovery
      │
      ▼
libp2p RPC
      │
      ▼
Metadata Retrieval
```

This architecture keeps networking responsibilities clearly separated while leveraging existing libp2p protocols.

