# Collaboration Opportunities

As maintainers and contributors within the libp2p ecosystem, we believe there are several exciting opportunities for collaboration.

These are intended as discussion topics rather than proposals.

---

## Network Observability

Large peer-to-peer systems are often difficult to operate without visibility into network behavior.

Potential collaboration areas include:

* DHT lookup latency
* connection establishment
* relay utilization
* NAT traversal diagnostics
* transport negotiation
* peer churn
* routing visualization
* resource management

Better networking observability would benefit both AGNTCY operators and libp2p developers.

---

## Application-Level Observability

Beyond networking itself, distributed agent systems introduce higher-level operational questions.

Possible areas include:

* agent discovery latency
* RPC performance
* publication propagation
* federation health
* CID resolution
* request tracing
* service availability

This complements existing networking metrics with application-level insights.

---

## Agent Ecosystem Interoperability

The broader AI ecosystem is rapidly evolving around multiple protocol families.

Examples include:

* SLIM
* Model Context Protocol (MCP)
* Agent-to-Agent (A2A)
* OpenTelemetry
* AGNTCY Identity
* emerging agent communication protocols

libp2p could continue serving as a common networking substrate beneath these protocols rather than requiring each ecosystem to implement its own networking layer.

---

## Hybrid Networking Models

One particularly interesting research direction is combining

* centralized services
* decentralized discovery
* secure peer identities
* enterprise deployments
* public peer-to-peer infrastructure

Hybrid deployments may help organizations adopt decentralized networking incrementally while maintaining operational requirements.

---

## Routing Research

Future experimentation may include

* capability-aware routing
* semantic discovery
* trust-aware routing
* locality-aware peer selection
* enterprise federation
* adaptive routing algorithms

These ideas build naturally on existing libp2p routing primitives.

---

## Discoverability

Beyond discovering peers, future work could explore discovering

* capabilities
* skills
* services
* APIs
* tools
* models

This represents an evolution from peer discovery toward richer agent discovery.

---

# Why This Matters

Distributed AI systems increasingly require

* secure identities
* scalable networking
* decentralized discovery
* interoperability
* resilience
* federation

These challenges closely align with the problems libp2p has been solving across distributed systems for many years.

By building upon established networking protocols, AGNTCY can focus its innovation on the agent layer while benefiting from ongoing improvements across the broader libp2p ecosystem.

